(160, 12, 'JavaScript is a', 'JavaScript es un', 'JavaScript is a popular programming language used for web development.\r\nYou can use let to declare a variable that may change later.\r\nIf you use const, the value cannot be changed.\r\nTo show a message on the screen, use console.log(\"Hello World\");.\r\nFunctions are blocks of code that perform a task.\r\nA function can be declared with the keyword function.\r\nExample: function greet(name) { return \"Hello \" + name; }\r\nYou can call a function like this: greet(\"Anna\");.\r\nUse if to run code only if a condition is true.\r\nif (x > 10) { console.log(\"x is greater than 10\"); }\r\nYou can also use else or else if for other cases.\r\nArrays store multiple values in one variable.\r\nExample: let colors = [\"red\", \"blue\", \"green\"];\r\nAccess array items by index: colors[0] is \"red\".\r\nUse a for loop to repeat code a number of times.\r\nExample: for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) { console.log(i); }\r\nObjects are collections of key-value pairs.\r\nExample: let user = { name: \"Ana\", age: 30 };\r\nAccess object data with dot notation: user.name.\r\nEvents are actions like clicks or key presses.\r\nYou can add an event listener with addEventListener.\r\nExample: button.addEventListener(\"click\", function() { alert(\"Clicked!\"); });\r\nArrow functions are a shorter way to write functions.\r\nExample: let sum = (a, b) => a + b;\r\nJavaScript is used to make websites interactive and dynamic.\r\nIt runs in the browser without needing to refresh the page.', '[{\"content\":\"JavaScript is a popular programming language used for web development.\",\"translation\":\"JavaScript es un lenguaje de programaci\\u00f3n popular utilizado para el desarrollo web.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 12:59:42\"},{\"content\":\"JavaScript is a popular programming language used for web development.\",\"translation\":\"JavaScript es un lenguaje de programaci\\u00f3n popular utilizado para el desarrollo web.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 12:59:44\"}]', 0, NULL, '2025-07-25 20:08:22'),
(162, 12, 'JavaScript Array Methods', 'Métodos de matriz de JavaScript', 'JavaScript Array Methods List with English Descriptions\r\n\r\nBasic array methods\r\n\r\npush adds an element to the end of the array\r\npop removes the last element from the array\r\nunshift adds an element to the beginning of the array\r\nshift removes the first element from the array\r\nconcat combines two or more arrays into one\r\njoin joins all elements of the array into a string\r\nslice returns a portion of the array without modifying it\r\nsplice adds removes or replaces elements in the array modifying the original\r\nindexOf returns the index of the first matching element\r\nlastIndexOf returns the index of the last matching element\r\nincludes checks if an array contains a specific element\r\nreverse reverses the order of the elements in the array\r\nsort sorts the elements in the array alphabetically or numerically\r\n\r\nIteration and transformation methods\r\n\r\nforEach executes a function once for each array element\r\nmap creates a new array by applying a function to each element\r\nfilter creates a new array with elements that pass a test\r\nfind returns the first element that satisfies a test function\r\nfindIndex returns the index of the first element that satisfies a test\r\nevery returns true if all elements pass a test\r\nsome returns true if at least one element passes a test\r\nreduce applies a function to reduce the array to a single value\r\nflat flattens nested arrays into a single level array\r\nflatMap maps and then flattens the result into a new array\r\n\r\nAdditional useful methods\r\n\r\nfill fills all or part of the array with a static value\r\ncopyWithin copies part of the array to another location in the same array\r\nat returns the element at a specific index supports negative indexing\r\ntoString converts the array to a string\r\nArray isArray checks whether a variable is an array\r\n\r\nJavaScript Functions\r\n\r\nFunctions are reusable blocks of code that perform a task\r\n\r\nFunction declaration example\r\n\r\nfunction greet name returns Hello followed by the name\r\n\r\nArrow functions\r\n\r\nArrow functions are a shorter syntax for writing functions\r\n\r\nExample of arrow function that adds two numbers\r\n\r\nconst add equals open parenthesis a comma b close parenthesis arrow a plus b\r\n\r\nIf the function has only one parameter you can omit the parentheses\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nconst square equals x arrow x times x\r\n\r\nArrow functions are useful for callbacks and concise code\r\n\r\nJavaScript Variables\r\n\r\nVariables store data values\r\n\r\nYou can declare variables using var let or const\r\n\r\nLet is block scoped and preferred over var\r\n\r\nConst is used for constants that do not change\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nlet count equals 0\r\n\r\nconst pi equals 3 point 1416\r\n\r\nYou can update let variables but not const variables\r\n\r\nJavaScript Conditionals\r\n\r\nConditional statements allow decision making in code\r\n\r\nIf statement runs code if a condition is true\r\n\r\nElse runs code if the condition is false\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nif count greater than 10 open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log Count is greater than ten\r\n\r\nclose brace else open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log Count is ten or less\r\n\r\nclose brace\r\n\r\nJavaScript Loops\r\n\r\nLoops repeat code multiple times\r\n\r\nFor loop runs code a fixed number of times\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nfor let i equals zero semicolon i less than five semicolon i plus plus open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log i\r\n\r\nclose brace\r\n\r\nWhile loop runs code while a condition is true\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nwhile count less than five open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log count\r\n\r\ncount plus plus\r\n\r\nclose brace', 'Unchift agrega un elemento al comienzo de la matriz', 0, NULL, '2025-08-06 09:12:45'),
(163, 12, 'The Mysterious Letter', NULL, 'The Mysterious Letter\r\n\r\nYesterday morning, I found a strange envelope on my small wooden desk, but I didn’t open it immediately.\r\nShe told me she had never seen it before, although her curious eyes followed my hands while I touched it.\r\nInside, there was an old photograph of two young boys holding their father’s large, weathered hat under the sunlight.\r\nI remembered my grandfather once mentioning a secret he had kept hidden in a box beneath his bed.\r\nWithout thinking, I placed the letter in my coat pocket and walked quickly toward the quiet park near our street.\r\nWhile I was sitting on the cold bench, a tall man approached me, asking politely if I was Mr. Collins.\r\nI said I wasn’t, yet I noticed he still looked at me as if he knew my family’s history.\r\nHe explained that his brother had written the letter twenty years ago, but it was lost during a stormy night.\r\nI asked him why it had appeared on my desk, and he simply smiled, pointing at the photograph in my hand.\r\nSuddenly, I realized the younger boy in the picture was wearing my father’s silver watch, the one he always carried.\r\nHe told me I should keep the letter safe, because one day it might help me find something I had been missing.\r\nBefore I could reply, he turned around, disappeared into the misty street, and left me holding a mystery in my pocket.\r\nI walked home slowly, wondering if my life had just changed, or if it was simply another strange morning in my quiet town.', '[{\"content\":\"The Mysterious Letter\",\"translation\":\"La misteriosa carta\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 13:23:58\"},{\"content\":\"The Mysterious Letter\",\"translation\":\"La misteriosa carta\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 13:24:00\"},{\"content\":\"Yesterday morning, I found a strange envelope on my small wooden desk, but I didn\\u2019t open it immediately.\",\"translation\":\"Ayer por la ma\\u00f1ana, encontr\\u00e9 un sobre extra\\u00f1o en mi peque\\u00f1o escrito